article.headline: Towson 40, Villanova 19
article.story:
TOWSON, Md. (AP) -- Josh Corle returned a blocked punt 28 yards,
Trent Covington scored on a 70-yard fumble recovery and Towson
rolled up 38 first-half points in a 40-19 victory over Villanova on
Saturday.

The Tigers (6-3, 3-3 Atlantic 10) recorded five sacks, recovered
two fumbles, intercepted two passes and blocked two conversion
kicks, returning one for two points.

Martin Gibson, Christopher Polite and Matt Dicken scored
touchdowns for Villanova (4-5, 2-4 Atlantic 10). Frank Jankowski
was 24-for-43 for 245 yards for the Wildcats.

Towson's Sean Schaefer completed 18 of 29 passes for 192 yards.

The Wildcats stalled on the game's opening drive and Andrae
Brown blocked Adam James' punt. Corle picked up the ball and
sprinted 28 yards for a 7-0 lead after just 1:40. Towson went up
14-0 when Kerry Miles' 1-yard dive capped a seven-play, 43-yard
drive midway through the first quarter.

Later, Jankowski coughed up the ball on a sack and Towson
recovered at the 21. The Tigers needed only four plays before
Schaefer scored on a 1-yard sneak with 2:32 left in the period.

Ron Halbruner's 23-yard field goal early in the second quarter
made it 24-0, but Gibson scored on a 3-yard run with 6:24 left in
the first half.

Fifty-five seconds later, Schaefer found Marcus Lee alone behind
the defense for an 84-yard touchdown, a career long for both
players. On the Wildcats' next series, Jankowski fumbled when he
was sacked by Marcus Edwards and Covington scooped up the loose
ball for a 70-yard touchdown return with 2:03 remaining.
